{"word":"ἀμφίλεκτος","slug":"ἀμφίλεκτος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀμφίλεκτος</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>discussed on all hands, doubtful</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: so <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-τως</el>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>disputatious</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>ἀμφ. εἶναί τινι</el> <i>to quarrel for</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}